tellegen
Copyright 2026 Samuel Talkington and contributors

tellegen is a differentiable power flow and optimal power flow engine in Rust: the DC
optimal power flow and locational marginal price sensitivities, the AC power flow
voltage sensitivities, the full nonlinear AC optimal power flow, and the SOCWR (Jabr)
conic relaxation of AC optimal power flow, each with analytic sensitivities. Licensed
under the Apache License 2.0 or the MIT License, at your option.

The W-space SOCWR formulation follows the standard Jabr second-order-cone relaxation
(R. A. Jabr, 2006) as implemented in PowerModels.jl
(https://github.com/lanl-ansi/PowerModels.jl, BSD-3-Clause), used as a formulation
reference; the implementation here is independent.

Third-party components (optional `acopf-pounce` feature). Enabling the pounce backend
for the full nonlinear AC optimal power flow links:

- pounce (pounce-nlp, pounce-algorithm, pounce-common, pounce-linalg, pounce-linsol,
  pounce-feral, pounce-qp, pounce-presolve, pounce-l1penalty, pounce-observability):
  Eclipse Public License 2.0 (EPL-2.0), https://crates.io/crates/pounce-nlp. These
  components remain under the EPL-2.0; their source is available on crates.io and a
  copy of the EPL-2.0 accompanies any binary that bundles them.
- FERAL (feral, feral-amd, feral-amf, feral-metis, feral-scotch, feral-kahip,
  feral-ordering-core), pure-Rust sparse ordering/linear-algebra: MIT License.

`acopf-pounce` is off by default, so the engine's default build stays Apache-2.0 / MIT;
enabling it adds the EPL-2.0 components above.

